## Description {#details}

Implementation of the target library information.

This class constructs tables that hold the target library information and make it available. However, it is somewhat expensive to compute and only depends on the triple. So users typically interact with the <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetlibraryinfo">TargetLibraryInfo</a></code> wrapper below.

The vector-functions library defines, which functions are vectorizable and with which factor. The library can be specified by either frontend, or a commandline option, and then used by addVectorizableFunctionsFromVecLib for filling up the tables of vectorizable functions.
